1. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the pasta until just tender, about 12 minutes. Drain and set aside. 2. Melt the butter in a large pot over medium-low heat and quickly saut√©the vegetables until just tender. Do not overcook. Season well with salt and pepper. Add the half-and-half and cook to thicken the sauce, 5 minutes. Season well with pepper. Toss in the drained pasta and sprinkle with Parmesan. Garnish with diced tomatoes and chives or pea shoots, if available. Serve immediately.